'''''Bored of the Rings''''' is a [[interactive fiction|text adventure]] game released by [[Delta 4]] in [[1985 in video gaming|1985]] for several computer systems<ref name=WoS>{{WoS game|id=0006036|name=Bored of the Rings}}</ref> written using [[The Quill Adventure System|The Quill]].<ref name=WoS/><ref name=SU>[http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/040/advent.htm "Richard Price sets out on the road to Rivendull while Tolkien turns in his grave"], [[Sinclair User]] 7.85, page 96. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070812191800/http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/040/advent.htm |date=2007-08-12 }}</ref> It was also released by [[CRL Group]]. The game is inspired by, but not based on, the ''[[Bored of the Rings]]'' parody novel published by [[Harvard Lampoon]].<ref>[http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/045/htsquad.htm "Bored out of his skull"], [[Sinclair User]], 12.85, page 66. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070912124318/http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/045/htsquad.htm |date=September 12, 2007 }}</ref> The earlier game ''[[The Hobbit (1982 video game)|The Hobbit]]'' is also parodied. It was followed by a prequel in the same spirit, ''[[The Boggit]]''.<ref name=WoS/>

== Plot ==
Fordo the Boggit, Spam, Pimply and Murky must take the Great Ring to Mount Gloom.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/details/sinclair-user-magazine-040/page/n95/mode/1up?view=theater | title=Sinclair User Magazine Issue 040 | date=July 1985 }}</ref>

== Gameplay ==
The game is a standard [[interactive fiction|text adventure]] with static background graphics in some locations. It accepts verb / noun commands and also short sentence inputs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://worldofspectrum.org//pub/sinclair/games-info/b/BoredOfTheRings.txt|title=Bored Of The Rings (c) 1985 Delta 4 Software|website=worldofspectrum.org|access-date=19 August 2023}}</ref> It was split into three parts with parts two and three requiring password input to access.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gb64.com/oldsite/gameofweek/14/gotw_boredofrings.htm|title=gamebase64.com - The Gamebase Collection|website=www.gb64.com}}</ref>

